 the spring, the firm expects\nto haul general freight from meat\nto staples and furniture.\nLoaded trucks, according to a\ntentative schedule set last week,\nare to leave Seattle for Anchor\nage every Monday, Wdnesdav, and\nFriday. A truck will leave Fari\nbanks every Tuesday and Thurs\nday.\nEach truck will be manned by\ntwo men.\nnual convention of the national re- j\ntail dry goods association in New i\nYork, and their main objective is\nto increase sales, lower their costs\nand maintain profits.\nThe experts don\u2019t look for a gen\neral price break, nor for a busi\nness recession, but they do look\nfor a general selective downward\nprice revision and a general in\ncrease in value and style where\nprices aren\u2019t reduced from present\nlevels.\nI\nAlaska Airlines\nNOW\nNOME to\nEVERETT WASH.\nSTARLINER\nDC-4\nScheduled Daily\nFROM ANCHORAGE\nFREIGHT RATE\nNOME to EVERETT\n22 Cen ts per pound\nVUiiiiliiylSPBtfV\nWXLN _\nFriday, January 14. 1949\n5:00\u2014News\n5:15\u2014Lum and Abner\n5:30--Time Fur Music\n6:00\u2014AFKS Sports Reel\n6:15\u2014Words With Music\n6:30\u2014From the Bookshelf of the\nWorld\n7:00\u2014The Hawthorne Thing\n7:30\u2014California Melodies\n8:00\u2014On The Beam\n8:30\u2014Harvest of Stars\n9:00\u2014You Asked For It\n9:45\u2014Today\u2019s American\n10:00\u2014Screen Guild Players\n10:30\u2014Melodv Hour\n11:00\u2014Sign Off\nSaturday. January 15, 1949\n7:00 a.m.\u2014Red Harper\n7:15\u2014Sunrise Serenade\n7:45\u2014Morning Devotions\n8:00\u2014Let\u2019s Pretend\n8:30\u2014Record Shop\n9:00\u2014Morning Melodies\n9:15\u2014G I Jive i\n9:30\u2014Coffee Shop\n9:45\u2014Bob Carlton\n10:00\u2014Turntable Time\n10:30\u2014Heard At Home\n11:00\u2014Impressions In Melody\n11:30\u2014Album Music\nNoon\u2014V Disc Varieties\n12:30\u2014VVXLN News\n12:45\u2014Hymns From Home\n1:00\u2014Around the World in Music\n1:15\u2014Sound Off\n1:30\u2014You\u2019ll Be Surprised\n2:00\u2014Musical Varieties\n2:30\u2014Westward Ho\n3:00\u2014Matinee Me