ns on\nthe airfield here. The designer,\nHans Berger, ol\u2018 Thun, says his 1st\nfull- cale experimental ear will\nhave a maximum speed of 72 m.\np.h.\nThe first test model is only six\nfeet long and three feet wide. Its\nmotive power is supplied entirely\nby a small jet engine in the rear,\nwhich expels gas and air under\nhigh pressue and pushes the car\n\u2018orward. The car has no drive\nshaft, clutch, gears or differential.\nHogs need from 10 to 18 per cent\nof protein in their ration.\n9:30\u2014Coffee Shop\n9:45\u2014Chiquita\n10:00\u2014Turntable Time\n10:30\u2014Heard At Home\n11:00\u2014Impressions In Melody\n11:30\u2014Album Music\n11:45\u2014Personal Album\nNoon\u2014V Disc Varieties\n12:30\u2014WXLN News\n12:45\u2014At Ease\n1:00\u2014Around the World in Music\n1:15\u2014Club Fifteen\n1:30\u2014You\u2019ll Be Surprised\n2:00\u2014Musical Varieties\n2:30\u2014Westward Ho\n3:00\u2014Matinee Melodies\n4:00\u2014Strike Up The Band\n4:15\u2014Jerry Wayne\n4:30\u2014One Night Stand\n5:00\u2014News\nMuii} Labor Laws\nTo Come Before\nLegislature\np\nJU?T2V.T, M') Se e>- r\nures proposed by i bor for sro\nmission to the .\\1j3 iu\nwe.e outline bv T- d r n\nmissioner ot labor Henry Benson\nin a talk before the CIO conven\ntion Wednesday.\nThey included: Amendments to\nthe unemployment compensation\nlaws which will provide compen\nsation for workers when ill and\nincrease compensation for unem\nployed with families; wage collec\ntion system which will include a\nlien against property for protec\ntion of wage claims\nA retirement plan for municipal\nTerritorial employees who do not\nreceive social security benefits; a\nwage-hour law providing a mini\nmum payment of $1 an hour with\ntime and a half after eight hours\nin one day or 40 hours in a week.\nIssuance of work permits for\nminors; a law providing equal pay\nfor women; and the establishment\nof an apprenticeship division in\nthe department of labor to formu\nlate standards and supervise ap\nprenticeships, to